cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with blind source separation (BSS) problem using a regularized Fast Multichannel Nonnegative Matrix Factorization (FastMNMF) with prior information for joint diagonalization of the spatial covariance matrix model. This involves optimization techniques and signal processing methods, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SI (Signal Processing), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
